UVdIjmtvhQF_8D39iXHw] (the most subtle and circumspect of the stagnationist=
 books), he identifies non-technological factors as contributing to the sta=
gnation, and he predicts that both technology and productivity growth will =
bounce back. Stagnationists would be well-advised to read that book!

